wer54w66sf32re2

title: 3. CHRISTMAS CUBES
info:
CHRISTMAS CUBES

ingredients

1 c. peppermint candy pieces
2 c. plain chocolate cookies
1 c. whipped cream

preparation

Put candy and cookies in separate bags. Crush with rolling pin until both are fine crumbs. Mix into whipped cream. Place mixture into an ice cube tray. Freeze. Cut into small squares to serve. Serves 8.

title: 13. PARTY PUNCH
info:
PARTY PUNCH

ingredients

1 large can frozen orange juice concentrate
1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice
1 large pkg. cherry gelatin
1/2 gal. orange sherbet
2 qt. lemon-lime soda

preparation

Blend juices and gelatin in punch bowl. Stir in sherbet and soda. Makes 40 cups.

title: 10. CHOCOLATE NUT BREAD
info:
CHOCOLATE NUT BREAD

ingredients

1 3/4 c. all-purpose flour
1/3 c. cocoa
1/4 c. dry buttermilk
1/4 c. sugar
1 tsp. cinnamon
1 tsp. baking soda
1 tsp. baking powder
1 c. water
1/2 c. vegetable oil
1/4 c. liquid egg substitute (at room temperature)
liquid sugar substitute to equal 1/3 c. sugar
1 tsp. vanilla
1/2 c. chopped nuts

preparation

Place flour, cocoa, dry buttermilk, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder in bowl and mix at low speed to blend well. Mix water, oil, egg, sweetener and vanilla with a fork to blend. Add to flour mixture and mix at medium speed only until flour is moistened. Add nuts to dough and spread evenly in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan which has been greased with margarine. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean from the center and the bread pulls away from the sides of the pan. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out on wire rack to cool to room temperature.

title: 3. "LITE FRUIT SALAD"
info:
"LITE FRUIT SALAD"

ingredients

1 small box sugar-free vanilla instant pudding
1 (16 oz.) can chunk pineapple
1 (16 oz.) can fruit cocktail
grapes
1 to 2 bananas, sliced

preparation

Optional: Other canned fruits may be added if desired.

Drain and discard juice from fruit cocktail. Drain and save juice from pineapple. Mix juice with pudding. Mix all fruit together and stir in pudding mixture. Chill and serve.

title: 9. NO ROLL PASTRY
info:
NO ROLL PASTRY

ingredients

3 oz. cream cheese
1 stick oleo
1 c. plain flour

preparation

Cream together and press into pie plate. Bake in oven about 20 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake.

title: 9. CRANBERRY - NUT BREAD
info:
CRANBERRY - NUT BREAD

ingredients

1 c. whole-wheat flour
1 c. white flour
1/4 c. sugar
1 Tbsp. baking powder
2 tsp. grated orange rind
1 c. orange juice
2 Tbsp. vegetable oil
1 egg
1 c. chopped fresh or frozen cranberries
1/3 c. raisins
1/3 c. chopped walnuts

preparation

Combine the flours, sugar, baking powder and orange rind in a mixing bowl. Add the remaining ingredients and stir until well blended. Pour into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool for 5 to 7 minutes before removing from pan. Turn onto a wire rack and cool thoroughly. Store in a plastic bag or aluminum foil for at least 1 day before slicing. Serves 15.

title: 12. CHRISTMAS SCENT
info:
CHRISTMAS SCENT

ingredients

3 to 4 inch cinnamon sticks
3 bay leaves
1/4 c. whole cloves
1/2 lemon
1/2 orange
1 qt. water

preparation

Put all ingredients in a tea kettle or saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer as long as desired. Add water as needed. This is not to eat or drink!

title: 10. BAGEL BITES
info:
BAGEL BITES

ingredients

1 tsp. reduced-calorie margarine, softened
1/4 tsp. dried whole oregano
1/8 tsp. garlic powder
2 (1 oz.) frozen mini bagels, thawed and halved

preparation

Combine first 3 ingredients and spread 1/4 teaspoon margarine mixture over cut sides of each bagel half. Place bagel halves, cut side up, on a baking sheet; broil 6 inches from heat for 1 minute or until golden brown. Yields 4 halves.

Per Serving: 94 Calories, 2 g. Fat (19%), 0 mg. Cholesterol and 119 mg. Sodium.

title: 8. KINDERGARTEN THANKSGIVING SOUP
info:
KINDERGARTEN THANKSGIVING SOUP

ingredients

6 c. beef broth
1/4 c. potato, diced
1/2 c. carrots, diced
1/2 c. celery, diced
2 Tbsp. onion, diced
1/4 c. alphabet macaroni pasta

preparation

Bring beef broth to a boil in a soup pot. Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onion. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add alphabet macaroni. Simmer 5 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: 11. SPINACH STUFFED PIZZA
info:
SPINACH STUFFED PIZZA

ingredients

3 cloves garlic, diced
1 bundle green onions
1/2 tsp. cayenne pepper
1/2 tsp. basil
1 pkg. soy Mozzarella cheese, shredded
7 bundles fresh organic spinach (may substitute with frozen spinach)
1 tsp. rosemary
1 tsp. vegie-sal
dash of kelp
1 pkg. soy Cheddar cheese, shredded

preparation

You will also need a pizza pan or round cooking sheet.

Prepare bottom layer of crust and top layer of crust.

Wash spinach to prepare for cooking. Cut spinach into pieces. Add all ingredients. Save a portion of cheeses for topping spinach. Put all ingredients on bottom layer of crust on cooking sheet or pizza pan. Top spinach with cheese. Put top crust layer on. Preheat oven to 250°. Bake for 45 minutes. Watch closely. Do not let crust burn. Make sure spinach is cooked. Cut into pizza shape and serve.

title: 5. BANANA PUDDING
info:
BANANA PUDDING

Servings: 4
Cuisine: American

ingredients

4 eggs
2 c. sugar
2 c. milk
1 tsp. vanilla extract
2 tsp. cornstarch
6 bananas
1 pkg. vanilla wafers

preparation

Put eggs in a boiler and beat well. Add sugar; mix well. Add milk. Cook slow until it gets to a boil, then add vanilla extract, then cornstarch (mixed in a little milk just to make a paste). Add to the pudding. This will thicken and will be ready to finish. Cut the bananas, put in bowl and add 1 layer of wafers. Add some pudding mix. Continue until all is finished.

notes

wer54w66sf32re2

title: 4. CORNED BEEF STEW
info:
CORNED BEEF STEW

ingredients

1 (12 oz.) can corned beef
1/2 c. chopped onion
1/4 c. chopped celery
1/4 c. chopped green pepper
1 Tbsp. oil
2 c. water
4 potatoes, cubed
1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes
1 Tbsp. catsup
1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce
1 tsp. instant beef bouillon granules

preparation

Cut meat in cubes. In a Dutch oven cook onion, celery and pepper in oil until tender. Add water, potatoes, tomatoes, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon granules and bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in corned beef and cook 2 minutes more.

title: 1. GRILLED SANDWICHES
info:
GRILLED SANDWICHES

ingredients

1 c. chopped ham
1/2 c. chopped Velveeta cheese
4 hard-boiled eggs, chopped
1 small onion, chopped fine
4 tsp. relish
1/2 c. salad dressing

preparation

Mix all ingredients together. Spread thick on buns. Wrap in foil. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven. Can be frozen before baking.

title: 15. VIENNA BOILED BEEF
info:
VIENNA BOILED BEEF
(Weiner Tafelspitz)

ingredients

water
2 large carrots, cut in thin sticks
1 tsp. salt
4 celery stalks, cut in thin strips
3 lb. beef brisket
2 leeks (white part only)
2 gherkins
1 onion, cut in rings
parsley

preparation

Heat 2 quarts water with salt. Add beef; bring to a boil. Skim foam from surface until clear. Partially cover pot; simmer 1 1/2 hours. Cut leeks in 2-inch pieces, then cut in half lengthwise. Add leeks, onion, carrots and celery to beef. Cook until beef and vegetables are tender. Cut beef into 1/2-inch slices. Cut gherkins lengthwise in thin slices, leaving 1 end uncut. Spread out slices like a fan; garnish beef with gherkins. Serve vegetables in a separate dish with 4 tablespoons cooking liquid spooned over the top. Garnish with parsley. Serve with Swedish mayonnaise.

title: 7. "LITE" BROCCOLI SOUP
info:
"LITE" BROCCOLI SOUP

ingredients

1 1/2 c. broccoli, chopped
2 ribs celery, chopped
1 onion, chopped
1 c. chicken broth
2 c. skim milk
2 Tbsp. cornstarch
1/4 tsp. salt
1/8 tsp. pepper
1/8 tsp. ground thyme

preparation

Simmer vegetables until tender in chicken broth. In medium bowl, combine milk, cornstarch, salt, pepper and thyme. Add milk mixture to vegetables; cook until soup is slightly thick, stirring constantly. Makes 4 servings.

Each serving contains 112 calories, 3 g fat, 9 mg cholesterol, 14 g carbohydrates and 257 mg sodium.

title: 2. CHOCOLATE BOTTOM CUPCAKES
info:
CHOCOLATE BOTTOM CUPCAKES

ingredients

8 oz. cream cheese
1 egg
1/3 c. sugar
1/2 tsp. salt
6 oz. pkg. chocolate chips
1 1/2 c. flour
1/4 c. cocoa
1 c. sugar
1 tsp. baking soda
1/2 tsp. salt
1 c. water
1/2 c. oil
1 Tbsp. vinegar
1 tsp. vanilla

preparation

Blend the first 4 ingredients, then stir in chocolate chips; set aside. Blend the remaining ingredients and fill paper-lined cups with this mixture 1/3 full. Drop 1 tablespoon of the cream cheese mixture into each cup. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 11. CHRISTMAS ANGEL CAKE
info:
CHRISTMAS ANGEL CAKE

ingredients

1 pkg. Duncan Hines angel food cake mix
2 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen sliced strawberries, thawed
1 pkg. strawberry flavored gelatin
1 c. hot water
confectioners sugar

preparation

You will need cardboard.

Day Before: Prepare angel cake mix as label directs, baking it in an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Cool cake as directed, then store, carefully covered.

Drain thawed strawberries, reserving the syrup (about 1 to 1 1/4 cups). Dissolve gelatin in hot water, then stir in reserved strawberry syrup. Refrigerate until slightly thickened, about 1 hour. Fold drained berries into this mixture. Refrigerate until almost set, about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

Meanwhile, with serrated knife, cut inverted angel cake crosswise into 3 even layers; place bottom layer on cake plate. Over it, spread half of strawberry-gelatin mixture almost to edge. Adjust second layer, top side up. Over it, spread rest of gelatin mixture. Cover with top layer. Refrigerate.

From cardboard, cut eight 2-inch stars, then lay them, in a circle, around center top of cake. Now generously sprinkle top and sides of cake with confectioners sugar. Carefully lift off cardboard stars, leaving star pattern on cake. Refrigerate cake about 1/2 hour or until ready to serve. Serve in small wedges. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

This is a beautiful cake, with the red strawberry mixture shimmering through the white confectioners sugar.

title: 14. CAJUN BLACKENED FISH
info:
CAJUN BLACKENED FISH

ingredients

4 Tbsp. margarine, melted
4 fish fillets
1/2 tsp. onion powder
1/2 tsp. garlic powder
1/2 tsp. white pepper
1/2 tsp. black pepper
1/2 tsp. cayenne pepper
1/8 tsp. thyme
1/8 tsp. sage
1/8 tsp. oregano

preparation

Spread melted margarine over fillets. Combine all spices and mix well. Rub spices into fish. Heat cast-iron skillet until very hot; watch carefully. Cook fillets for about 3 minutes on each side, depending on thickness. (Caution: Cook outside or in very well ventilated area.)

title: 14. ICED TEA DRINK
info:
ICED TEA DRINK

ingredients

5 Tbsp. instant tea
1 pkg. orange drink powdered mix
1 can frozen lemonade, partially thawed
2 1/2 c. sugar
1 gal. cold water

preparation

Mix all ingredients together. Serve over ice cubes.

title: 10. CHICKEN WING APPETIZERS
info:
CHICKEN WING APPETIZERS

ingredients

40 baby drumsticks
14 oz. bottle ketchup
1 c. apple cider vinegar
dash of Worcestershire sauce
1 tsp. dry mustard
1 tsp. ginger
1 c. brown sugar
1 c. sugar

preparation

Place chicken wings in single layer in shallow roasting pan. Mix remaining ingredients together. Heat on top of stove until sugar is dissolved. Pour sauce over chicken wings. Place, uncovered, in a 350° oven and bake for approximately 2 hours. Turn wings occasionally. After first hour, check frequently to prevent burning. Wings are done when sauce is thick and bubbly.

title: 15. CREOLE FISH ORLEANS
info:
CREOLE FISH ORLEANS

ingredients

1/4 c. Promise margarine
1 large onion, chopped (1 c.)
1/2 c. sliced celery
1 tsp. minced garlic
1 (16 oz.) can 50% less salt tomatoes (undrained), cut in pieces
1 bay leaf
1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce
1/4 tsp. salt
1/8 tsp. hot pepper sauce
1 c. sliced fresh mushrooms
1 1/2 lb. fish fillets (sole, flounder or turbot)

preparation

In large skillet, melt Promise; sauté onion, celery and garlic 3 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce, salt and hot pepper sauce. Simmer 15 minutes or until thickened. Add mushrooms. Roll fillets. Arrange in sauce. Cover. Cook 10 minutes longer or until fish is done. Remove fish to serving platter. Remove bay leaf from sauce; discard. Spoon sauce around fish; sprinkle with parsley if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: 15. READY TO DRINK ICED TEA
info:
READY TO DRINK ICED TEA

ingredients

3 qt. medium strength tea
1 1/2 c. sugar
1 qt. ginger ale
1 (12 oz.) can frozen lemonade concentrate

preparation

(Steep 2 family-size tea bags in 3 quarts of water.)

Combine tea, sugar and concentrate. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and pour over crushed ice in glasses.

title: 1. CHOCOLATE PUDDING DESSERT
info:
CHOCOLATE PUDDING DESSERT

ingredients

1 c. flour
1/2 c. butter or margarine
1 c. finely chopped pecans
1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese, softened
1 c. powdered sugar
1 (8 oz.) frozen whipped topping, thawed
1 (4 oz.) pkg. instant vanilla pudding mix
1 (4 oz.) pkg. instant chocolate pudding mix
3 c. milk
1 (1.45) milk chocolate bar, grated

preparation

Mix flour and butter together until they form small crumbs. Stir in pecans. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Fold in half of the whipped topping. Spread over cooled crust.

Place contents of both packages of pudding mix into large bowl. Add milk and beat slowly with rotary beater for 2 minutes or until smooth. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.

Let stand a few minutes, then carefully spread remaining whipped topping over top. Sprinkle with grated chocolate. Cover and refrigerate.

title: 12. ORIENTAL VEGETABLES
info:
ORIENTAL VEGETABLES

ingredients

1 Tbsp. molasses or brown sugar
1 Tbsp. each: soy sauce and vinegar
1 tsp. grated fresh ginger root
1 c. green onions, bias sliced into 1/4-inch lengths
6 oz. fresh pea pods or 1 (6 oz.) pkg. frozen pea pods
2 c. shredded Chinese cabbage or cabbage
1 c. thin bite-size strips green or sweet red pepper
1 c. fresh bean sprouts

preparation

Stir together molasses or brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar; set aside. Spray a wok or large skillet with nonstick spray coating. Stir-fry ginger root over medium-high heat for 30 seconds (wok or skillet should be preheated). Add onions and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add pea pods and cabbage and stir-fry for 2 more minutes. Add green or sweet red pepper and bean sprouts; stir-fry for 1 minute more or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Pour sauce over vegetables and toss to coat. Heat through. Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

Per Serving: 41 Calories, 0 g. Fat, 0 mg. Cholesterol and 196 mg. Sodium.

title: 10. CHEDDAR CHEESE SCALLOPED POTATOES
info:
CHEDDAR CHEESE SCALLOPED POTATOES

ingredients

1 1/2 c. skim milk
2 Tbsp. all-purpose flour
1/2 tsp. salt or seasoned salt
1/8 tsp. pepper
1/8 tsp. garlic powder (optional)
1/2 c. chopped onion
4 medium potatoes, peeled and thinly sliced
1/2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese (2 oz.)
snipped fresh parsley (optional)

preparation

Stir together milk, flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Stir in onion.

Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick spray coating. Place half the potatoes in the casserole. Top with half the sauce; repeat layers with remaining potatoes and sauce. Bake in a 350° oven, covered, about 65 minutes or until potatoes are tender (stir once). Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. If desired, garnish with parsley. Serves 8.

Per Serving: 118 Calories, 3 g. Fat, 8 mg. Cholesterol and 208 mg. Sodium.

title: 11. PARTY PUNCH
info:
PARTY PUNCH

ingredients

1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice
1 (6 oz.) can frozen orange juice
1/2 c. powdered sugar
1/4 c. fresh lemon juice
1 large bottle ginger ale

preparation

Have all juices chilled. Combine pineapple and orange juices; melt powdered sugar in lemon juice and add. Add ginger ale just before serving. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: 4. ORANGE SLUSH DRINK
info:
ORANGE SLUSH DRINK

ingredients

9 c. water
1 1/2 c. sugar
1 (12 oz.) frozen orange juice concentrate
1 (12 oz.) frozen lemonade concentrate
2 c. vodka or gin

preparation

Bring water and sugar to boil. Add remaining ingredients to cooled water/sugar mixture. Place in empty Cool Whip or butter containers and freeze overnight.

For serving, fill glass with 3/4 slush mixture, then add 50/50 or Squirt to fill glass.

title: 6. ORANGE SLUSH DRINK (JULIUS)
info:
ORANGE SLUSH DRINK (JULIUS)

ingredients

6 oz. frozen orange juice (we think Bright and Early orange juice tastes best)
1 c. milk
1 c. water
1/2 c. sugar
1 tsp. vanilla
15 to 20 ice cubes

preparation

Do all in blender until frothy.

title: 5. VEGETABLE RICE BAKE
info:
VEGETABLE RICE BAKE

ingredients

2 tsp. instant chicken bouillon granules
2/3 c. long grain rice
1/2 c. chopped green pepper
2 c. shredded zucchini or chopped broccoli
1/2 tsp. each: onion powder, basil and oregano
2 beaten eggs
1 c. skim milk
1/8 tsp. pepper
3/4 c. shredded low-fat Cheddar cheese
1/2 (8 oz.) container reduced-calorie soft-style cream cheese
2 Tbsp. diced pimiento

preparation

Bring bouillon granules and 1 1/2 cups water to a boil in a saucepan; add rice. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until rice is tender. In a medium saucepan, combine 1/2 cup water and green pepper; bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 minutes. Add zucchini or broccoli. Cover; simmer for 3 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender; drain well. Set aside. Combine eggs, milk, onion powder, basil, oregano and 1/8 teaspoon pepper in a large mixing bowl. To hot rice, stir in Cheddar cheese and cream cheese; stir the rice cheese/mixture into the egg mixture. Finally add cooked vegetables and pimiento. Spoon into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until center is set. Serves 4.

Per Serving: 315 Calories, 12 g. Fat, 169 mg. Cholesterol and 574 mg. Sodium.

title: 12. VEGGIE PIZZA
info:
VEGGIE PIZZA

ingredients

2 pkg. Pillsbury crescent rolls (8 roll size)
1 c. mayonnaise
8 oz. cream cheese
1/2 pkg. Hidden Valley Ranch dressing
cut up vegetables
Cheddar cheese, grated

preparation

Pat crescent rolls into an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Cool. Spread mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing over crust. Top with cut up vegetables such as cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, fresh mushrooms, green peppers, black or green olives and tomatoes. Grate Cheddar cheese on top. Cut into squares.

title: 14. SALMON DIP
info:
SALMON DIP

ingredients

1 (7 3/4 oz.) can flaked salmon
1 c. sour cream
3 Tbsp. chopped green onion
1 Tbsp. lemon juice
1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce
1/2 tsp. dill
1/4 tsp. salt
dash of bottled hot pepper sauce

preparation

Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: 12. CHERRY DESSERT SALAD
info:
CHERRY DESSERT SALAD

ingredients

1 can cherry pie filling
1 small can crushed pineapple, drained
1 c. nuts, chopped
1 can sweetened condensed milk
1 c. small marshmallows
whipped topping
1 c. coconut (optional)

preparation

Mix all ingredients together with the exception of the whipped topping. Top the salad with the topping. Refrigerate overnight.

title: 5. CHICKEN WINGS ON THE GRILL
info:
CHICKEN WINGS ON THE GRILL

ingredients

1 lb. chicken wings
1/2 bottle Italian dressing

preparation

Marinate chicken wings in the Italian dressing overnight. Grill over low heat for 30 minutes; turn and grill 30 minutes more. Enjoy!

title: 4. PARTY TIME PORK CHOPS
info:
PARTY TIME PORK CHOPS

ingredients

1/2 c. packed brown sugar
3 Tbsp. cider vinegar
2 tsp. spicy brown mustard
1/2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce
4 pork chops

preparation

Combine brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Brush each pork chop with sugar mixture. Preheat grill; cook chops about 4 inches from heat source, basting occasionally with sugar mixture. Cook until chops are done.

title: 10. CHICKEN KABOBS ON GRILL

title: 8. BAKED PIZZA SPAGHETTI
info:
BAKED PIZZA SPAGHETTI

ingredients

1 1/2 lb. hamburger
1 medium onion, chopped
2 (6 oz.) cans tomato paste
2/3 c. water
1 (4 oz.) can mushrooms
1/2 tsp. oregano
1 (6 oz.) pkg. broken vermicelli
1/4 c. melted butter
1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese
1 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese

preparation

Brown hamburger and drain well. Add onion, tomato paste, water, mushrooms and oregano. Cook vermicelli; drain and toss with melted butter. Combine vermicelli, meat mixture and the Cheddar cheese. Stir well until blended. Pour into 2 1/2 quart casserole dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: 9. Bagel Bites
info:
Bagel Bites

Servings: 1

ingredients

1 tsp. reduced-calorie margarine, softened
1/4 tsp. dried whole oregano
1/8 tsp. garlic powder
2 (1 oz.) frozen mini bagels, thawed and halved

preparation

Combine first 3 ingredients and spread 1/4 teaspoon margarine mixture over cut sides of each bagel half. Place bagel halves, cut side up, on a baking sheet; broil 6 inches from heat for 1 minute or until golden brown. Yields 4 halves.

Per Serving: 94 Calories, 2 g. Fat (19%), 0 mg. Cholesterol and 119 mg. Sodium.

notes

wer54w66sf32re2

title: 3. MUSHROOM TOFU QUICHE
info:
MUSHROOM TOFU QUICHE

ingredients

12 oz. tofu (fresh bean curd), drained and cut up
2 egg whites
1 egg
1/3 c. skim milk
1/2 tsp. dried oregano, crushed
1/8 tsp. garlic powder
3/4 c. shredded low-fat Cheddar cheese
1/4 tsp. pepper
1/8 tsp. salt
1 (7 oz.) can whole kernel corn with sweet peppers, drained
1 Tbsp. dried minced onion
1 tsp. margarine
2 Tbsp. fine dry bread crumbs
1 medium tomato, cut in thin wedges
1 Tbsp. snipped fresh parsley (optional)

preparation

Combine tofu, egg whites, whole egg, milk, oregano, garlic powder, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/8 teaspoon salt in blender. Cover and blend or process until smooth. Stir in corn and dried onion. Prepare a 9-inch pie plate by spreading margarine over the bottom and sides and sprinkling with bread crumbs. Pour tofu mixture into pie plate. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (a knife inserted near the center should come out clean). Arrange tomato wedges on top of quiche and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake until cheese is melted (about 3 minutes). Garnish with parsley. Makes 4 servings.

Per Serving: 212 Calories, 10 g. Fat, 83 mg. Cholesterol and 411 mg. Sodium.

title: 1. ROCKY ROAD CAKE
info:
ROCKY ROAD CAKE

ingredients

1 c. chopped walnuts
1 c. seedless raisins
1 c. miniature marshmallows
1 (6 oz.) pkg. semi-sweet chocolate pieces
1 (18 1/2 oz.) pkg. devil's food cake mix with pudding in the mix
4 eggs
1 c. Hellmann's mayonnaise
1 c. water

preparation

Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan or Bundt pan. In small bowl, mix walnuts, raisins, marshmallows and chocolate pieces. In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat together cake mix, eggs, mayonnaise and water just until blended. Increase speed to medium; beat for 2 minutes. Stir in nut mixture. Pour in prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove. Cool on rack. If desired, dust with confectioners sugar. Makes 12 servings.

title: 14. CRANBERRY APPLE OR BLUEBERRY APPLE MUFFINS
info:
CRANBERRY APPLE OR BLUEBERRY APPLE MUFFINS

ingredients

1 c. cranberries (fresh) or 1 c. blueberries
1 egg
1/2 c. milk
1/4 c. salad oil
1 1/2 c. all-purpose flour
1/2 c. sugar
2 tsp. baking powder
1/2 tsp. salt
1 apple, peeled and diced

preparation

Preheat oven to 400°. Beat egg; stir in milk and oil. Mix in remaining ingredients until moistened. Apple should be peeled and diced. Cranberries should be halved. (Batter should be lumpy.) Bake 20 minutes or until slightly browned. Makes 12 to 15 muffins. Enjoy!

title: 15. THANKSGIVING DRESSING
info:
THANKSGIVING DRESSING

ingredients

2 15 x 11 pans of day old bread
1 bunch chopped celery
1 large onion
2 sticks butter
1 cooked and cut up chicken
1/2 tsp. pepper
6 slightly beaten eggs
1 tsp. poultry seasoning
2 tsp. salt or more to taste

preparation

Put day old bread slices on cake pans in oven at 250° until slices are browned. After cooled, soak browned slices a few seconds in water. Squeeze out water well and gently. Put bread in large bowl. Brown chopped celery, onion, and butter together. Add this to bread. Next, fold in cut up chicken (cooked). Lastly, add rest of ingredients. Stir gently. Stuff turkey and put rest of dressing in a 10 x 7 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. All stuffing ingredients are already cooked except eggs, so this doesn't need to be overbaked.

title: 2. PASTA AND CAULIFLOWER SOUP
info:
PASTA AND CAULIFLOWER SOUP

ingredients

1 small cauliflower head
1/2 c. olive oil
1 garlic clove
salt to taste
pepper to taste
1 Tbsp. tomato paste
2 1/2 qt. hot water
1 potato, sliced paper thin
2 tsp. salt
1/2 lb. linguine or spaghetti, broken into bits
3 to 4 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese

preparation

Break the cauliflower into its flowerets, cutting the bigger ones in halves or quarters so that all the pieces are about 1/2-inch in size. Put the oil in a soup pot along with the garlic, salt, pepper and the cut-up cauliflower. Stirring gently, cook over medium heat until the vegetable bits are well oiled and flavored. Add the tomato paste, hot water, the potato slices and 2 teaspoons salt and bring to a boil. Break the pasta into 1 or 2-inch lengths as you put it in the pot. Continue boiling until the pasta is well cooked, has absorbed some of the water and the cauliflower, garlic and tomato have lent their flavors to the pasta. Before serving discard the garlic clove. Serve with a sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.

title: 10. CHRISTMAS CHEER DESSERT
info:
CHRISTMAS CHEER DESSERT

ingredients

1/4 c. creme de menthe
1 pt. lime sherbet, softened
1 qt. vanilla ice cream, softened
1 pkg. Dream Whip, prepared per directions on pkg.

preparation

Mix all together with mixer and refreeze.

title: 3. PEANUT SAUCE FOR PASTA
info:
PEANUT SAUCE FOR PASTA

ingredients

1/4 c. creamy peanut butter
2 Tbsp. hot water
1 Tbsp. cider vinegar
1 Tbsp. soy sauce
1 tsp. sugar
1 Tbsp. salad oil
1/2 tsp. hot pepper sauce
1 (8 oz.) pkg. pasta

preparation

In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, beat peanut butter with water until smooth. Stir in vinegar and next 4 ingredients until blended. Add cooked and drained pasta; toss gently to coat well. Serve immediately.

title: 2. FRUIT DIP
info:
FRUIT DIP

ingredients

2 (8 oz.) fruit flavored cream cheese
2 (7 oz.) jars marshmallow cream
1 small container Cool Whip

preparation

Cream the cream cheese; add marshmallow cream. When well blended, add Cool Whip. Serve with chunks of cantaloupe, honeydew melon, pineapple, apple, banana, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: 3. THANKSGIVING BREAD
info:
THANKSGIVING BREAD

ingredients

1/2 c. dried apricots
1/2 c. dates
1 c. chopped walnuts
3 c. flour
3 tsp. baking powder
1/4 tsp. baking soda
1 1/2 tsp. salt
1 c. brown sugar
1 egg, lightly beaten
1 c. milk
1/2 c. maple syrup

preparation

Cover apricots with hot boiling water 15 minutes and drain. Mix fruit and nuts. Sift dry ingredients. Add brown sugar and blend well. Add egg and milk, then syrup. Stir all well. Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Let stand 15 to 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: 8. PASTA SALAD DRESSING
info:
PASTA SALAD DRESSING

ingredients

2 cloves garlic, crushed
1/2 c. salad oil
1 tsp. salt
1 tsp. dry mustard
1 tsp. white pepper
2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce
6 anchovy fillets
3 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese
2 eggs
2 Tbsp. lemon juice

preparation

Combine all ingredients and puree until smooth. Add and toss with pasta and veggies.

title: 5. CHOCOLATE COCA-COLA CAKE
info:
CHOCOLATE COCA-COLA CAKE

ingredients

2 c. flour
1 tsp. soda
2 c. sugar
2 sticks margarine
1 c. Coca-Cola
3 Tbsp. cocoa
1/2 c. buttermilk
2 eggs, beaten
1 tsp. vanilla
2 c. small marshmallows

preparation

Mix flour, soda and sugar. Heat margarine, Coca-Cola and cocoa over medium heat to boiling point. Pour over flour mixture and stir. Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows. Batter will be thin. Bake in well-greased 3-quart Pyrex pan (13 x 9-inches) for 35 minutes at 350°. Top with favorite frosting.

title: 2. BAKED FISH WITH APRICOT SAUCE
info:
BAKED FISH WITH APRICOT SAUCE

ingredients

1 1/2 lb. fresh or frozen halibut or other lean fish steaks, cut 1-inch thick
1/4 tsp. garlic salt
1 (16 oz.) can unpeeled apricot halves (in light syrup)
1 Tbsp. cornstarch
1 to 2 tsp. curry powder
1 tsp. soy sauce
1/8 tsp. ground ginger
1/2 (8 oz.) can sliced water chestnuts
1/4 c. sliced green onions

preparation

If using frozen fish, thaw. Cut into 6 equal portions and arrange in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle fish with garlic salt; set aside.

Apricot Sauce: Drain apricots, reserving syrup. Cut apricot halves in two; set aside. Stir together reserved apricot syrup, cornstarch, curry powder, soy sauce and ginger in a small saucepan; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in apricots, water chestnuts and green onions. Spoon over fish.

Bake at 450°, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Makes 6 servings.

Per Serving: 188 Calories, 2 g. Fat, 33 mg. Cholesterol and 194 mg. Sodium.

title: 7. VEGETABLE SOUP
info:
VEGETABLE SOUP

ingredients

3 c. strong chicken broth
1 c. water
2 c. canned tomatoes, drained and coarsely chopped
1 onion, coarsely chopped
1 large or 2 small cloves garlic, finely chopped
2 stalks celery, finely chopped
2 carrots, peeled and sliced
1/2 tsp. chili powder
pinch of cayenne
salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
1 1/2 c. fresh or thawed frozen corn kernels
3 medium zucchini, sliced into rounds
2 Tbsp. chopped fresh parsley
freshly grated Parmesan cheese

preparation

In a large pot, combine the broth, water, tomatoes, onion, garlic, celery, carrots and seasonings. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add the corn, zucchini and parsley and continue to simmer for an additional 10 minutes. Adjust the seasonings and serve hot with a light sprinkling of Parmesan cheese. Serves 6.

title: 7. BAKED SQUASH AND APPLES
info:
BAKED SQUASH AND APPLES

ingredients

2 medium cooking apples, cored and cut into 1/2-inch thick round slices
lemon juice to taste
1 3/4 lb. acorn squash, cut in 1/2-inch thick round slices
2 Tbsp. raisins
dash of ground cinnamon
2 Tbsp. reduced-calorie pancake and waffle syrup

preparation

Preheat oven to 350°. Brush apple slices with lemon juice to prevent browning. Layer squash and apples in a 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with raisins and cinnamon. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.

Before serving, drizzle squash and apples with syrup. Makes 4 servings.

Per Serving: 106 Calories, 0 g. Fat, 0 mg. Cholesterol and 22 mg. Sodium.

title: 4. CAESAR-STYLE CHICKEN SALAD
info:

title: 13. HONEY CHICKEN WINGS APPETIZER
info:
HONEY CHICKEN WINGS APPETIZER

ingredients

3 lb. chicken wings
1 c. honey
2 Tbsp. vegetable oil
1/2 garlic clove, chopped
1/2 c. soy sauce
2 Tbsp. catsup
salt and pepper

preparation

Cut off and discard wing tips. Cut each wing into two parts and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Place wings in slow cooker and pour sauce over. Cook all day on low setting. Or, preheat oven to 375°. Place wings in shallow casserole and pour sauce over and bake 1 hour until chicken is well done and sauce is caramelized. Serves 10.

title: 10. THANKSGIVING PUMPKIN CHIFFON PIE
info:
THANKSGIVING PUMPKIN CHIFFON PIE

ingredients

1 envelope Knox gelatine
1/4 c. cold water
1 1/4 c. canned pumpkin
1/2 c. milk
1/2 tsp. each: ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt
1 c. sugar
3 eggs, separated

preparation

To slightly beaten egg yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, salt and spices. Cook until thick in double boiler. Soften gelatine in cold water. Add to hot pumpkin mixture. Mix thoroughly and cool. When it begins to thicken, fold in mixture of egg whites and 1/2 cup of sugar. Pour in shell and chill.

title: 11. BEEF SHISH KABOBS
info:

title: 11. CAULIFLOWER WITH CHEESE AND CHILI SAUCE
info:
CAULIFLOWER WITH CHEESE AND CHILI SAUCE

ingredients

1 medium head cauliflower (1 1/2 lb. total; remove leaves and trim stem)
1/4 c. chopped onion
1/4 c. chopped green or sweet red pepper
1/4 c. water
1/3 c. skim milk
1 Tbsp. all-purpose flour
1/2 c. (2 oz.) shredded sharp Cheddar cheese
2 Tbsp. canned chopped green chili peppers
dash of hot pepper sauce

preparation

Cook cauliflower in a small amount of boiling salted water in a large saucepan for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender; drain.

Cook onion and green or red pepper in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes or until tender in a covered saucepan. Stir together milk and flour until smooth and stir into vegetable mixture. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, then continue to cook for 1 minute more. Stir in cheese until melted. Stir in green chili peppers and hot pepper sauce; heat through. Place cauliflower on a serving plate and pour some of the cheese sauce over the top. Pass the remaining sauce. Makes 6 servings.

Per Serving: 66 Calories, 3 g. Fat, 10 mg. Cholesterol and 155 mg. Sodium.

title: 10. CHOCOLATE PISTACHIO CAKE
info:
CHOCOLATE PISTACHIO CAKE

ingredients

1 box white or yellow cake mix
1 c. water or 1/2 c. orange juice and 1/2 c. water
4 eggs
1/2 c. oil
1 box pistachio instant pudding (3 1/2 oz.)
3/4 c. chocolate flavored syrup

preparation

Combine first 5 ingredients. Blend to moisten, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour about 3/4 of batter into well greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Add 3/4 cup chocolate-flavored syrup to remaining batter. Mix well. Pour over batter in pan. Run knife through batter to marbleize. Cook for 1 hour or until done. Cool. Sprinkle with confectioners 10x sugar or cover with chocolate icing.

title: 7. CHICKEN WING APPETIZERS
info:
CHICKEN WING APPETIZERS
(Makes 36 Appetizers)

ingredients

1/2 c. plain yogurt
1/3 c. A.1. steak sauce
2 Tbsp. honey
56 Ritz crackers, finely rolled (about 2 c. crumbs)
1/2 c. sesame seed
18 chicken wings, split, discard tips (about 3 lb.)

preparation

In small bowl, blend yogurt, steak sauce and honey. In pie plate, combine cracker crumbs and sesame seed. Dip chicken pieces in steak sauce mixture, then coat with crumb mixture. Arrange on greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done, turning after 15 minutes.

Microwave: Prepare chicken wings as directed. Place half the wings in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-proof baking dish. Microwave, uncovered, on High (100% power) for 12 minutes or until chicken is tender, rearranging wings after 6 minutes. Repeat with remaining chicken wings.

title: 12. PEACH, BLUEBERRY OR BLACKBERRY CRISP
info:
PEACH, BLUEBERRY OR BLACKBERRY CRISP

ingredients

1 pkg. (pt. or more) berries or peaches
1 c. plain flour
1 c. sugar
3/4 c. brown sugar
1 egg
1 tsp. baking powder
oleo

preparation

Place berries or peaches in long baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot liberally with oleo. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and egg until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over fruit. Bake 45 minutes or until brown on top in 350° oven.

title: 15. NO-ROLL PASTRY
info:
NO-ROLL PASTRY

ingredients

1 c. all-purpose flour
1/2 tsp. salt
1/4 c. plus 2 Tbsp. shortening
2 to 3 Tbsp. cold water

preparation

In medium bowl with fork, stir flour with salt. With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle cold water into flour mixture, a tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with fork after each addition, until pastry is just moist enough to hold together. Press to bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate. Flute edge; cover with plastic wrap.

title: 2. GERMAN CHOCOLATE UPSIDE-DOWN CAKE
info:
GERMAN CHOCOLATE UPSIDE-DOWN CAKE

ingredients

1 c. chopped pecans
1 c. coconut
1 (2 layer) German chocolate cake mix
1 c. melted margarine
8 oz. cream cheese softened
1 (16 oz.) pkg. confectioners sugar

preparation

Sprinkle pecans and coconut in buttered cake pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Spoon into prepared pan. Combine remaining ingredients in mixer bowl; beat until smooth. Spoon evenly over cake, leaving 1-inch edge. Bake for 50 minutes. Cool in pan. Cut into squares. Invert squares on serving plates. Makes 20 servings in pan size 9 x 13-inch.

Note: Cream cheese mixture will sink to bottom during baking to form frosting.

title: 8. BANANA PUDDING
info:
BANANA PUDDING

ingredients

4 eggs
2 c. sugar
2 c. milk
1 tsp. vanilla extract
2 tsp. cornstarch
6 bananas
1 pkg. vanilla wafers

preparation

Put eggs in a boiler and beat well. Add sugar; mix well. Add milk. Cook slow until it gets to a boil, then add vanilla extract, then cornstarch (mixed in a little milk just to make a paste). Add to the pudding. This will thicken and will be ready to finish. Cut the bananas, put in bowl and add 1 layer of wafers. Add some pudding mix. Continue until all is finished.

title: 15. MOCHA CAKE
info:
MOCHA CAKE

ingredients

2 c. flour
2 c. sugar
3/4 c. cocoa
2 tsp. baking soda
1 tsp. baking powder
1/2 tsp. salt
1/2 c. oil
1 c. milk
1 c. coffee (liquid)
2 eggs

preparation

Preheat oven to 350°. Put ingredients in bowl one by one. Beat with electric mixer 2 to 4 minutes, batter will be thin. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan or two round pans with margarine and then dust with flour. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Test for doneness with a toothpick or a cake tester. Always test cake in the center of the cake.

title: 3. EASY NO ROLL PASTRY SHELL
info:
EASY NO ROLL PASTRY SHELL

ingredients

1 1/2 c. flour
1 1/2 tsp. sugar
3/4 tsp. salt
1/2 c. salad oil
2 Tbsp. milk

preparation

Combine flour, sugar and salt in 9-inch pie pan. Mix with fork. Beat oil and milk together with fork. Mix with flour mixture until evenly dampened. Press with fingers in even layer over bottom, up sides and partially cover rim. Flute edges. This is a rich, crumbly crust.

title: 13. BARBECUED CHICKEN
info:
BARBECUED CHICKEN

ingredients

2 1/2 lb. broiler, quartered and skinned
1/4 c. water
1/4 c. vinegar
2 Tbsp. chili sauce
1 tsp. salt
1/4 tsp. pepper
1 tsp. paprika
1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce
1/4 tsp. mustard
1/2 tsp. liquid noncalorie sweetener
2 Tbsp. grated onion
1 clove garlic, minced

preparation

Preheat oven to 375°. Place quartered chicken in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in pan; bring to a boil. Pour sauce over chicken. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Yields 4 servings. Contains 125 calories per serving.

title: 8. CHOCOLATE FUDGE ICE CREAM CAKE
info:
CHOCOLATE FUDGE ICE CREAM CAKE

ingredients

1/2 lb. margarine or butter
1 c. sugar
1 tsp. vanilla
4 eggs
1 c. flour
1 1/2 tsp. baking powder
1 1/2 tsp. baking soda
pinch of salt
1 lb. can chocolate syrup
1 qt. vanilla ice cream
1 pt. chocolate ice cream
6 oz. chocolate chips
small amount milk (not more than 1/4 c.)
chopped nuts

preparation

Cream butter and sugar until light and creamy. Add vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add alternately with chocolate syrup to creamed mixture. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Freeze when cool.

Soften ice creams and mix together. Spread over frozen cake and refreeze. Melt chocolate chips and add milk until creamy. Drizzle over cake. Top with chopped nuts and return to freezer. Cut in squares.

title: 12. MEDITERRANEAN PASTA SALAD
info:
MEDITERRANEAN PASTA SALAD

ingredients

2/3 c. olive oil
3 Tbsp. red wine vinegar
2 Tbsp. fresh basil
1/4 c. chopped green onions
2 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese
1/2 tsp. salt
1/4 tsp. black pepper
12 oz. rotelle pasta, freshly cooked and drained
1 each: small red, green and yellow bell peppers, halved lengthwise and cut in thin strips
1 medium tomato, cut in wedges
1/4 c. ripe black olives
8 oz. cubed Feta or Mozzarella cheese
1/4 tsp. dried oregano

preparation

Process oil, vinegar, basil, green onions, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in blender until smooth. Put pasta, bell pepper strips, tomato wedges and olives in large bowl. Pour in dressing; toss to mix. Roll cheese cubes in remaining 2 tablespoons basil to coat. Add to salad; sprinkle with oregano. Toss lightly. Serve at room temperature. Serves 4 main dish servings.

title: 14. THANKSGIVING FRUITCAKE
info:
THANKSGIVING FRUITCAKE

ingredients

1 c. oil
1 c. firmly packed brown sugar
4 eggs, separated
2 tsp. allspice
2 tsp. cinnamon
1 tsp. cloves
2 tsp. salt
1 tsp. baking powder
3 c. flour
1 c. fruit juice
1 1/2 c. chopped candied cherries
1 c. shaved lemon and orange rind
1 c. chopped figs
1 c. chopped candied pineapple
1 c. raisins
3 c. chopped nuts

preparation

Mix oil, sugar, and egg yolks in large mixing bowl. Beat well for approximately 2 minutes. Sift allspice, cinnamon, and cloves together. Add salt, baking powder and 2 cups of flour. Add flour mixture alternately with the fruit juice to the first mixture. Mix 1 cup flour with the fruits and nuts. Add to the batter. Beat 4 egg whites until stiff. Fold beaten egg whites into the batter mixture. Pour batter into a 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: 12. ITALIAN WEDDING SOUP
info:
ITALIAN WEDDING SOUP

ingredients

4 chicken breasts, skinned
3 qt. water
salt to taste
1/2 tsp. pepper
1 medium chopped onion
1/2 c. celery, diced
1 c. carrots, diced
1 pkg. frozen spinach
3/4 c. acini de pepe, cooked
1 small can mashed tomatoes
grated Parmesan cheese
1 Tbsp. parsley

preparation

Wash chicken; place in large pot with water and boil. Remove foam that forms. Add salt, pepper, onion, celery and carrots. Cook 2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove chicken and shred. Add spinach and already cooked pasta. Add shredded chicken and tomatoes. Cook 1/2 hour longer. More water may be added if necessary. Add cheese, garnish with parsley and serve while hot.

title: 2. APPETIZER CHICKEN WINGS
info:
APPETIZER CHICKEN WINGS

ingredients

5 lb. chicken wings (tips removed)
1 c. onions, chopped
2 garlic cloves
3 Tbsp. olive oil
2 Tbsp. honey
1/3 c. olive oil
1 Tbsp. curry powder
1 Tbsp. chili powder
1 tsp. pepper
2/3 c. soy sauce
1/3 c. lime juice

preparation

Saute onion and garlic in 3 tablespoons olive oil, then add remaining ingredients. Heat together until warm. Layer chicken wings in one layer in large flat baking dish/pan. Pour sauce over wings and bake 1 hour at 375°. Turn wings over at 30 minutes. Enjoy.

The sauce can also be used for a whole chicken or to marinate breasts too!

title: 5. THANKSGIVING GARDEN RELISH
info:
THANKSGIVING GARDEN RELISH

ingredients

3 c. chopped green peppers
1 c. chopped sweet red peppers
1 qt. chopped green tomatoes
1 c. chopped onion
1/4 c. salt
1 qt. cider vinegar
3/4 c. sugar
1/2 Tbsp. celery seed
1 Tbsp. mustard seed

preparation

Yields about 5 pints.

Chop all vegetables in a food chopper. Sprinkle them with the 1/4 cup of salt and let stand overnight; drain. Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seeds. Bring to boiling point. Add chopped vegetables and simmer for 10 minutes. Pour mixture in hot sterilized jars and seal. Be sure vegetables are covered with syrup.

title: 8. "QUICK AND EASY" SWEET AND SOUR CHICKEN
info:
"QUICK AND EASY" SWEET AND SOUR CHICKEN

ingredients

1 lb. boneless chicken, cut in cubes
2 Tbsp. oil
1 garlic clove, minced
1 c. green pepper strips
1 c. carrots strips
1 1/4 c. chicken bouillon
3 Tbsp. vinegar
3 Tbsp. brown sugar
1/3 c. teriyaki sauce
1 (8 oz.) can chunk pineapple in juice
1 1/2 c. instant rice

preparation

Saute chicken in oil until lightly browned. Add garlic, onion, pepper strips and carrots. Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes. Add bouillon, teriyaki sauce, vinegar, sugar and pineapple with juice. Bring to a full boil.

Stir in the rice. Cover and remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Stir before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: 1. PARTY SANDWICHES
info:
PARTY SANDWICHES

ingredients

1 loaf day old bread (white or wheat)
margarine or Miracle Whip
10 slices lunch meat
10 slices American cheese

preparation

Using assorted metal cookie cutters, cut shapes out of bread. Spread with margarine or Miracle Whip. Cut lunch meat and cheese out using same cookie cutters. Garnish each sandwich with pickle slice or green olive. For best results, be sure cookie cutters are sharp.

title: 2. CREAMY GREEN CHILE SOUP
info:
CREAMY GREEN CHILE SOUP

ingredients

1 c. chopped onion
1 c. chopped celery
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 Tbsp. reduced-calorie margarine
3 Tbsp. all-purpose flour
1 tsp. chicken-flavored bouillon granules
2 c. hot water
2 c. skim milk
1/4 tsp. chili powder
1/8 tsp. ground red pepper
2 (4 oz.) cans chopped green chiles, drained
1/4 c. plus 2 Tbsp. (1 1/2 oz.) shredded 40% less-fat Cheddar cheese

preparation

In a 3-quart casserole, combine onion, celery, garlic and margarine and cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Add flour; stir well. Dissolve bouillon in hot water. Gradually add bouillon, milk, chili powder and pepper to mixture and stir well. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring every 3 minutes. Stir in chiles and microwave on High for 1 minute. Stir well before serving.

To Serve: Ladle soup into individual serving bowl and top each bowl with 1 tablespoon cheese. Serve immediately. Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

Per Serving: 94 Calories, 2.7 g. Fat, 2 mg. Cholesterol, and 282 mg. Sodium.

title: 6. PARTY PINK SALAD
info:
PARTY PINK SALAD

ingredients

juice of No. 2 can crushed pineapple
24 large marshmallows
1 pkg. strawberry gelatin
2 c. cottage cheese
1 c. drained crushed pineapple
1 c. chopped pecans
1 (8 oz.) box Cool Whip

preparation

Combine pineapple juice and marshmallows. Place over low heat. Add gelatin. Melt marshmallows and dissolve gelatin. Add all other ingredients. Mix. Fold in Cool Whip last. Place in refrigerator. Will keep for several days.

title: 11. SUSHI IN FRIED BEAN CURD
info:

title: 6. CHRISTMAS BREAD
info:
CHRISTMAS BREAD

ingredients

1 c. butter
1 c. sugar
1 tsp. salt
2 eggs, beaten
3/4 tsp. cardamom
2 c. scalded milk
2 pkg. dry yeast, dissolved in 1/4 c. lukewarm water
7 c. flour
egg yolk
sliced almonds

preparation

Cream butter, sugar and salt. Add eggs and spice. Cool milk to lukewarm; add yeast. Blend milk mixture with 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add creamed mixture and remaining flour; mix until smooth. Let rise until doubled in bulk. Turn dough onto floured board. Divide into three equal portions. Put two portions aside. Divide remaining portion into three equal pieces. Shape each piece into a rope and then braid. Tuck ends under and place on greased cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining two portions. Let rise until almost doubled in bulk. Brush tops of loaves with egg yolk, mixed with a little bit of water. Sprinkle with sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serve with plenty of butter.

title: 3. SWEET AND SOUR BEEF STEW
info:
SWEET AND SOUR BEEF STEW

ingredients

2 Tbsp. oil
2 lb. beef stew meat
2 (8 oz.) cans tomato sauce
2 tsp. chili powder
2 tsp. paprika
1/4 c. sugar
1/4 c. vinegar
1/2 c. molasses
1 tsp. salt
2 c. carrots, sliced
2 c. onions, diced
1 green pepper, diced

preparation

Heat the oil and cubed stew meat and brown. Add tomato sauce, chili powder, paprika, sugar, vinegar, molasses and salt plus 1 cup water, and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add more water, if needed. Add the carrots, onions and green pepper and cook another 30 minutes.

Can be made in a crock-pot. Brown meat first and then add all the other ingredients. Cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 6 hours.

title: 7. GERMAN CHRISTMAS COOKIES
info:
GERMAN CHRISTMAS COOKIES

ingredients

2 1/2 c. granulated sugar
1 c. lard
1 pt. sweet milk
1 oz. baking ammonia
3 eggs
1/2 tsp. salt
1 tsp. oil of anise

preparation

Soak ammonia in milk 24 hours. Stir occasionally. Flour to make a stiff dough. Roll thin and cut with Christmas cookie cutters. Bake at 325° to 350° until light brown on bottom and white on top. Frost and decorate. Never a failure. They mellow after frosted and stored in an airtight container.

title: 2. STUFFED PEPPERS
info:
STUFFED PEPPERS

ingredients

4 medium green or sweet red peppers or a combination, cut in half lengthwise with seeds and membranes removed
2 (6 3/4 oz.) cans chunk-style chicken or 2 c. chopped, cooked chicken, drained
1 (7 oz.) can whole kernel corn, drained
1 (15 oz.) can Spanish rice
1/4 c. frozen sliced green onions
few dashes of bottled hot pepper sauce
1/4 c. finely shredded Cheddar cheese (1 oz.)

preparation

Place peppers, cut side down, in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap and cook on 100% power (High) for 6 to 8 minutes or until nearly tender, rearranging peppers after 3 minutes; drain. Break canned chicken into chunks. Combine chicken, corn, Spanish rice, frozen onions and pepper sauce in a 1 1/2 quart microwave-safe casserole. Stir until lightly mixed and cook, uncovered, on High about 6 minutes or until heated, stirring after 3 minutes. Turn peppers cut side up and mound chicken mixture into shells. Cook, covered, on High for 2 minutes or until heated and peppers are tender. Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand until cheese melts (about 2 minutes). Makes 4 servings.

Per Serving: 352 Calories, 13 g. Fat, 67 mg. Cholesterol and 1,024 mg. Sodium.

title: 9. THANKSGIVING ROLLS
info:
THANKSGIVING ROLLS

ingredients

1 c. mashed potatoes
1 1/2 c. potato water (warm)
2/3 c. sugar
1 1/2 tsp. salt
1 pkg. yeast
2 eggs, beaten
2/3 c. Crisco (butter-flavored)
6 1/2 to 7 c. bread flour, sifted

preparation

Have ready 1 cup mashed potatoes. Mix together warm water, sugar and salt. Mix yeast with this mixture. Add eggs and shortening; mix well. Add potatoes and mix well. Mix in flour and put in the refrigerator in a large container. Roll out on floured board and cut. Let rise about 3 hours. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: 1. EASY, EASY, EASY COOKIES
info:
EASY, EASY, EASY COOKIES

ingredients

1 box yellow cake mix (use devil's food mix for chocolate cookies)
2 eggs, beaten
1/2 c. vegetable oil

preparation

Mix all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove to rack to cool. I divide the batter and put pecans and pecan flavoring, coconut and coconut flavoring, orange or lemon flavoring, chocolate chips, peanut butter and butterscotch chips. I use a teaspoonful of dough and flatten with a fork. These are so easy to make.

title: 13. SHRIMP DIP
info:
SHRIMP DIP

ingredients

2 (4 1/2 oz.) cans shrimp, cooked and deveined
1 c. mayonnaise
1 c. sour cream
1/4 c. green onions
2 Tbsp. lemon juice
1/4 tsp. salt
1/8 tsp. pepper, ground
2 dashes of Tabasco sauce

preparation

Stir all ingredients until mixed well. Cover and chill. Serve with assorted crackers. Makes 3 cups.

title: 2. KIWI AND TANGERINE DELIGHT
info:
KIWI AND TANGERINE DELIGHT

ingredients

6 kiwi
1 orange
6 tangerines
1 can mixed fruit salad
lettuce leaves

preparation

Peel kiwi and section tangerines and orange. Open chilled fruit salad and pour in small glass serving dish. Place serving dish in the middle of a plate and spread lettuce leaves around it, forming a bed of lettuce leaves. Place kiwi, tangerine and orange slices around serving dish, alternating in a circle pattern. Chill and serve.

title: 9. CHUNKY PIZZA SOUP
info:
CHUNKY PIZZA SOUP

ingredients

1 Tbsp. olive oil
1 small onion, chopped
1 green pepper, chopped
1/2 c. sliced mushrooms
1 (28 oz.) can plum tomatoes, undrained
1 c. beef stock
1/4 c. fresh basil, chopped or 1 tsp. dry basil
1 c. thinly sliced pepperoni
1 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese
1/4 c. Parmesan cheese

preparation

In saucepan heat oil; add onion, pepper and mushrooms. Stir-fry until soft, but not browned. Add tomatoes, stock, basil and pepperoni; cook until heated through. Mix 2 cheeses; ladle soup into 4 ovenproof bowls. Sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese melts. Or microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Serve immediately with some warm crusty French bread. Makes 4 servings.

title: 4. STRAWBERRY SPINACH SALAD
info:

title: 7. RASPBERRY, BLUEBERRY OR BLACKBERRY PIE
info:
RASPBERRY, BLUEBERRY OR BLACKBERRY PIE

ingredients

1 qt. berries - washed and drained
1 cup water
1 cup sugar
3 tbsp. cornstarch
3 oz. package cream cheese, softened
1 9 inch baked, cooled pie shell

preparation

Save our 1/2 cup choice berries. Simmer 1 cup berries and 2/3 cup water about 3 minutes. Blend 1 cup sugar, 3 tbsp. cornstarch and 1/3 cup water and add to simmering mixture. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Cool. Spread cream cheese over bottom of crust. Put 2 1/2 cups berries over cream cheese and cover with cooked mixture. Garnish with the 1/2 cup berries. Refrigerate about 2 hours until firm. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: 15. HOT CHEESY SEAFOOD DIP
info:
HOT CHEESY SEAFOOD DIP

ingredients

1 lb. jalapeno process cheese, cut into 1-inch cubes
1 (3 oz.) pkg. cream cheese
1/4 c. margarine
1 (4 1/2 oz.) can small shrimp or crab meat
1 (4 oz.) can chopped green chilies
chopped green onions with tops

preparation

Combine jalapeno process cheese, cream cheese and margarine in top of double boiler. Bring water to boil and reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring frequently, until cheese melts. Stir in shrimp or crab meat and green chilies. Put mixture in chafing dish and sprinkle with onion tops. Serve warm with tortilla chips or your favorite crackers. Yields 4 cups.

title: 11. NO ROLL PASTRY SHELL
info:
NO ROLL PASTRY SHELL

ingredients

1 1/2 c. flour
1 1/2 tsp. sugar
1 tsp. salt
1/2 c. oil
2 Tbsp. cold milk

preparation

Sift dry ingredients into pie pan. Combine milk and oil in cup. Whip with fork and pour all at once over flour mixture. Mix until flour is completely dampened. Press evenly with fingers to line bottom of pan and up the sides. Be sure dough is pressed to uniform thickness. To flute: Prick entire surface. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°. For unbaked shell: Fill as desired and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: 9. CREAMY ITALIAN DIP
info:
CREAMY ITALIAN DIP

ingredients

1 (8 oz.) carton plain low-fat yogurt
1 pkg. Italian dressing mix
1 (12 oz.) carton low-fat cottage cheese

preparation

Blend all ingredients together in blender on high speed until smooth and creamy. Chill before serving. Yields 2 1/2 cups. Contains 8 1/2 calories per serving.

title: 3. CHOCOLATE CARROT CAKE
info:
CHOCOLATE CARROT CAKE

ingredients

2 c. sugar
4 eggs
1 1/2 c. oil
2 c. flour
2 tsp. soda
2 tsp. cocoa
1/2 tsp. salt
3 c. grated carrots
1 c. chopped nuts

preparation

Beat sugar, eggs and oil. Add dry ingredients, then carrots and nuts, mixing well. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 40 minutes. Frost when cool.

Cream Cheese Frosting:

ingredients

1 (3 oz.) pkg. cream cheese
1 Tbsp. milk
1 tsp. vanilla
1/2 tsp. salt
2 1/2 c. confectioners sugar

preparation

Blend cream cheese, milk, vanilla and salt. Gradually add sugar; beat until smooth. Add additional milk, 1 teaspoon at a time, if necessary.

title: 1. SPARKLING FRUIT SLUSH PUNCH (NON-ALCOHOLIC DRINK)
info:
SPARKLING FRUIT SLUSH PUNCH (NON-ALCOHOLIC DRINK)

ingredients

2 pt. unsweetened pineapple juice
2 (6 oz.) cans pink lemonade concentrate
1 c. water
juice of 1 lemon or lime

preparation

Mix ingredients and freeze overnight. Remove from freezer just before serving. Stir well. (Keeps in freezer.)

title: 2. EASY NO ROLL PASTRY SHELL
info:
EASY NO ROLL PASTRY SHELL

ingredients

1 1/2 c. all-purpose flour
1 1/2 tsp. sugar
3/4 tsp. salt
1/2 c. salad oil
2 Tbsp. milk

preparation

Combine flour, sugar and salt in 9-inch pie pan; mix with fork; beat oil and milk together with fork. Mix into flour mixture until evenly dampened; press with fingers in even layer over bottom, up sides and partially cover rim. Flute edges. This is a rich crumbly crust.

title: 13. "LITE" DILLED ROUND STEAK
info:
"LITE" DILLED ROUND STEAK
(Serves 4)

ingredients

1 lb. beef round steak, cut 3/4-inch thick
nonstick cooking spray
1 small onion
3/4 c. water
2 tsp. lemon juice
1 tsp. instant beef bouillon
1/8 tsp. garlic salt
1/4 tsp. dried dill weed
1/4 tsp. pepper
2 Tbsp. cold water
1 Tbsp. cornstarch

preparation

Trim fat from meat. Cut meat into 4 serving size pieces. Spray a cold large skillet with spray coating or add a little oil. Add meat and brown on medium heat. While meat is browning, thinly slice onion. Carefully add water, onion, lemon juice, bouillon, garlic salt, dill weed and pepper to skillet. Bring to boiling, then reduce heat. Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour until meat is tender.

Meanwhile, stir together cold water and cornstarch. To serve, transfer meat to platter. Cover to keep warm. Stir cornstarch mixture into juices. Cook, stirring over medium heat, until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Serve with meat. May double sauce recipe to use over rice.

title: 14. LEBANON NUT COOKIES
info:
LEBANON NUT COOKIES

ingredients

1 1/2 c. butter
3 c. sifted flour
1 1/4 c. finely chopped walnuts
1/3 c. granulated sugar
1/2 tsp. cinnamon
1 c. powdered sugar

preparation

With pastry blender or 2 knives scissor-fashion, cut butter into flour. Add about 1/4 cup water and toss quickly together, forming a smooth ball of dough. Form dough; break off walnut-size pieces. Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet. Make large indentation in center of each, forming little nests.

Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon; fill center of cookies. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown at 325°. Stir together powdered sugar and 5 teaspoons water. Use to dribble over cookies. Store, covered. Makes 40 to 50 cookies.

title: 12. CHOCOLATE-NUT BROWNIES
info:
CHOCOLATE-NUT BROWNIES

ingredients

1 sq. unsweetened chocolate or 1 oz. no-melt unsweetened chocolate
1/2 c. shortening
2 Tbsp. sweetener
2 tsp. vanilla
2 eggs, beaten
1 c. sifted flour
1/2 tsp. salt
1/2 tsp. baking soda
1/4 c. chopped nuts

preparation

Melt the unsweetened chocolate and shortening in a saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat. Add sweetener, vanilla and beaten eggs. Stir until well blended. Add flour, salt and baking soda. Mix until well blended. Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.

Substitution: Two brownies equal 1/2 bread and 1 1/2 fat substitutes.

title: 14. PARTY SALAD
info:
PARTY SALAD

1st Step:

ingredients

1 pkg. family size lemon or orange Jell-O, dissolved in 4 c. hot water
1 c. marshmallows
3 diced bananas
1 can chunk pineapple, drained

preparation

When Jell-O has set up and firmed, layer the top of Jell-O with marshmallows, bananas and pineapple.

2nd Step:

ingredients

1 can pineapple juice (from drained pineapple)
1/2 c. sugar
1 egg, well beaten
1 Tbsp. flour
1 small carton sour cream

preparation

Boil pineapple juice, sugar and egg until thick. When very cold, add sour cream. Mix well and spread over salad.

title: 11. SOFT DRINK DAIRY SLUSH
info:
SOFT DRINK DAIRY SLUSH

ingredients

4 or 5 oz. Dr. Pepper or other soft drink
4 or 5 oz. milk

preparation

Mix equal parts of Dr. Pepper (or other soft drink) and milk. Pour mixture into an 8 or 9-ounce cup. Freeze for 1 hour. Serve with a spoon.

title: 6. CARROT SALAD
info:
CARROT SALAD

ingredients

1 (8 oz.) can crushed pineapple (juice packed), drained (reserve 2 Tbsp. juice)
2 c. shredded carrot
1/2 c. sliced celery or chopped green pepper
1/2 tsp. finely shredded lemon peel
1 Tbsp. lemon juice
1 tsp. sugar or brown sugar
1/4 tsp. salt
dash of ground ginger
4 lettuce leaves (optional)

preparation

In a medium mixing bowl, combine drained pineapple, reserved pineapple juice, carrot, celery or green pepper, lemon peel, lemon juice, sugar, salt and ginger. Toss to coat well. Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve on lettuce-lined plates, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

Per Serving: 65 Calories, 0 g. Fat, 0 mg. Cholesterol and 169 mg. Sodium.

title: 12. ICE TEA DRINK
info:
ICE TEA DRINK

ingredients

1/4 vodka
1/4 gin
1/4 rum
1/4 Triple Sec

preparation

Splash of sour mix, fill glass with Coke.
